rater_note.pros: Incredible quality and immersive atmosphere that transcends Roblox, potential to become one of the best true horror games on the platform.
rater_note.cons: Gameplay, while currently decent, lacks standout features, scares could use some improvement for a more gripping experience.
rater_note.conclusion: Toshiko Tokyo Undying impresses with its amazing quality and atmosphere, almost making you forget you're in Roblox. The gameplay is solid, though not exceptional, but with future updates, it could be a top-tier horror game on Roblox.

rater_note.pros: Eerie atmosphere, unique and engaging gameplay, original despite being inspired by Five Nights at Freddy's.
rater_note.cons: Nothing specifically.
rater_note.conclusion: Submarine Simulator is a well-crafted, FNaF-inspired experience with unique gameplay and an unsettling atmosphere.

rater_note.pros: High quality textures, level design, and models contribute to impressive visual appeal.
rater_note.cons: Repetitive and frustrating gameplay experience. The game's concept has led to the creation of poorly designed mimic clones with subpar gameplay.
rater_note.conclusion: The game boasts astonishing visuals and overall production value, its gameplay leaves much to be desired.

rater_note.pros: Unique atmosphere/ambience that feels like Outlast, voice acting, pretty well-made.
rater_note.cons: Epilepsy jumpscare without warning, unoriginal gameplay, jumpscare in the sewers way too loud.
rater_note.conclusion: The first part of SANITY has great potential and was actually pretty good in regards of all categories, the sewers however dragged the whole game down a bit.

games.name: A Landscape of Thorns - The Spike Field

rater_note.pros: Everything concerning the visuals, bossfights.
rater_note.cons: Frustrating and inconsistent enemy AI, unnecessarily stretched out gameplay with small items that you have to find in a much too large area.
rater_note.conclusion: Although the game has astounding visual elements - especially models - it falls short in terms of gameplay and user experience.

rater_note.pros: Best Backrooms implementation in Roblox, stunning visuals, great atmosphere, and captivating presentation.
rater_note.cons: Levels can be too big and the low (hidden) stamina causes frustration.
rater_note.conclusion: As of now, it stands as the best implementation of the Backrooms in Roblox.

rater_note.pros: Very immersive experience with good animations and overall production.
rater_note.cons: There are no particular negative aspects; I just wish it would've been longer.
rater_note.conclusion: It's a very nice experience if you're looking for a quality short game that isn't too scary.

rater_note.pros: Good and rewarding puzzles, mysterious atmoshpere, and something a little different from others.
rater_note.cons: Sometimes the game is way too dark and the monster models seem sort of cheap.
rater_note.conclusion: The game offers rewarding puzzles and a captivating atmosphere, setting itself apart from others. However, excessive darkness and cheap monster models are notable drawbacks.

games.name: The cool obby! :D Winner gets a badge

rater_note.pros: Interesting flashlight mechanic and unique monster model.
rater_note.cons: Boring and unoriginal gameplay.

rater_note.pros: Everything concerning Night 1.
rater_note.cons: Low effort animations, buggy AI, everything concerning Night 2.
rater_note.conclusion: Night 1 delivers a captivating atmosphere and multiple endings, while Night 2 falls flat with nothing remarkable to offer.

rater_note.pros: Great visuals and ambience.
rater_note.cons: Bad performance, pretty much a copy of ROSES.
rater_note.conclusion: Hopefully an actually good and finished ROSES in the future.

rater_note.pros:
- One of the only Point and Click games I've seen on Roblox
- Different levels for different difficulty settings
- Effective jumpscare timing
rater_note.cons:
- Technically underdeveloped
- Unforgiving clickboxes and timer
- 3rd Level doesn't work
- Graphics are lacking
- It isn't clear on what you can click and models overlap in the inventory
rater_note.conclusion: Fun ideas that need a lot of polish and reworking. I suggest working on the existing chapters (updating textures and models + removing glitches) before adding any new content.
A worse remake of a mediocre mobile game.
Watch the gameplay here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0S-7q1CnBFU

rater_note.pros: Creating a horror IP in Roblox, Good animations for Roblox standards.
rater_note.cons: Boring and repetitive gameplay.
rater_note.conclusion: Rainbow Friends is notable for creating a horror franchise in Roblox. Sadly, the game itself isn't all that fun to play, despite being well made.
Read more about The Apartment 727 here: https://www.pcgamer.com/a-brief-history-of-moirai-one-of-pcs-most-disturbing-games/

rater_note.pros: The way the monster spawns right in front of you randomly is actually pretty scary.
rater_note.cons: Just another collectathon game with no special gameplay or ideas.
rater_note.conclusion: Average collectathon game with a kind of interesting monster mechanic.

games.name: A Farmer and His Scarecrow: Reborn

rater_note.pros: Better visuals and production than the original.
rater_note.cons: Because of the lackluster original, the remake  lacks appeal, dampening its overall impact.
rater_note.conclusion: It brings better production but still lacks appeal, making the remake fall short.

rater_note.pros:
- Rather unique scares
- Epic lobby music
rater_note.cons:
- Walking simulator
- Find the key
- Frustrating enemy constantly chasing you
- Too big of a maze
rater_note.conclusion: IT Lures follows the basic horror concept of entering an abandoned building that is being haunted, and therefore having to escape again. Other than finding the key, there are no gameplay mechanics, and except for some unconventional scares, this game does not deliver in any category.

rater_note.pros: Active updates that aim to improve the game.
rater_note.cons: Unnecessarily cumbersome backpack system, too dark even for its own name, basic uncreative gameplay.
rater_note.conclusion: We've been looking at this game for quite a while now. It went from having 6 Chapters to now having only a single one. It shows the developers care to actively update the game, however, it's just still not a rememberable experience.

rater_note.pros: The maze has a manageable size and the monster has a unique design.
rater_note.cons: Unoriginal boring gameplay as with all the other games like this one.
rater_note.conclusion: Despite a unique monster design, this game's disappointing choice of gameplay prevents it from being a standout.

rater_note.pros: - Anak Ni Lagim
rater_note.cons: - The game is unbeatable
rater_note.conclusion: There is just something about Anak Ni Lagim, that makes it some of the most fun we've had while doing this list, let's just call it "so bad it's good"

rater_note.pros: - Graphics were okay
rater_note.cons:
- Boring
- Chapter 2 is frustrating
rater_note.conclusion: This game has absolutely nothing going for it, except for a boring walking sim, there is nothing to be enjoyed in the slightest.

games.name: HERE, where the world is quiet

rater_note.pros: - Funny game, the giggle was very good
rater_note.cons:
- It wasn't scary
- Very long walking, with no sprinting option
rater_note.conclusion: There is nothing fun or scary about this game, there are a few moments of accidental comedy, but it's mostly an unplayable slog.
